ects as well as several important theories, revealing the lengths to which some have gone to claim success in identifying Jack the Ripper.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aSerial murdersxHistoryx19th centuryxEnglandxLondon. 0aSerial murderszEnglandzLondonxHistoryy19th century. 0aVictims of crimesxHistoryx19th centuryxEnglandxLondon. 0aVictims of crimeszEnglandzLondonxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aBennett, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030020707140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300207071423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300207071/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles